## Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package:**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to dependencies
- Used npm as the project's package manager

**2. Modified Files:**

**`app/layout.js`:**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag
- Follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router integration

**3. Updated Dependencies:**
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics to dependencies
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package resolution

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart) for Next.js App Router:

- The Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`app/layout.js`)
- Placed at the end of the `<body>` tag as recommended by the documentation
- This ensures analytics tracking works across all pages and routes in the application
- The component is a wrapper around the tracking script offering seamless Next.js integration

### Verification

✅ **Build Test:** Successfully ran `npm run build` - no errors
✅ **Linter Test:** Ran `npm run lint` - no new errors introduced by these changes
✅ **Package Installation:** All dependencies installed successfully

### Next Steps

To enable Web Analytics:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. After deployment, verify functionality by checking the browser Network tab for a Fetch/XHR request to `/<unique-path>/view`

### Notes

- The existing linting errors shown during the lint check are pre-existing issues in other files (admin/page.js, page.js, professor/[id]/page.js, components/Navbar.js, components/RequestProfessorModal.js) and are not related to the Analytics integration
- The Analytics component works immediately in development mode but will start collecting data once deployed to Vercel and enabled in the dashboard
